cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DL, cs.CYBER, cs.IR

Reasoning: The paper analyzes a dataset of scientists and their collaborations, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on collaborations and social behavior suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely categories. The analysis of the distribution of the number of collaborators and the gender differences in collaborations could also fit in cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the mention of interdisciplinary research and the differences observed in the natural sciences could suggest cs.CYBER (Cybernetics and Robotics).
